betterquesting.name: The Beginning [MR]
betterquesting.desc:
Welcome to Modern Skyblock!

 To start off, you are going to need to create or join an island and complete Stage 1 of it (make Dirt and a Sapling).
You can see all the different island types and how to complete Stage 1 of them in the Sky Resources guide, opened by pressing "G" (by default).

 You can grow your first few trees by twerking or sprinting around them, but you'll soon be able to craft Plant Matter and insta-grow them with it.

betterquesting.name: A Mob Farm [MR]
betterquesting.desc:
One of the main things that you are going to need in this pack and especially early on are mob drops. To obtain them you are going to need to make an enclosed room where mobs can spawn or a mob dropper.

 If something spawns while you're building it, in normal or easy mode, simply put any Tinker's Construct Frypan in a crafting grid and all your problems will be gone.

betterquesting.name: Dirt Furnace [MR]
betterquesting.desc: You can't craft a regular Furnace yet, so for cooking and smelting you are going to need the next best thing: a Dirt Furnace. It works just like a regular Furnace, but it uses 3 times more fuel.

betterquesting.name: Combustion [MR]
betterquesting.desc:
In order to make many basic items from Sky Resources and a few other mods, you are going to need to construct a multiblock Combustion Chamber.

 You can see how to do that and how to use it in the Sky Resources 2 guide.

betterquesting.name: Water Extractor [MR]
betterquesting.desc:
You can hold right-click and let go with a Water Extractor to collect Water from Leaves, Snow or Cacti.

 You can place Water by shift+right-clicking and with it make an infinite Water source.

betterquesting.name: Cobblestone [MR]
betterquesting.desc:
Now that you have Water and Lava, you can make a traditional Cobblestone Generator.

 If you're in normal or easy mode, you can turn any Tinker's Construct Pickaxe into a "Bane Of Cobble" Pickaxe, by simply putting it in a crafting grid.

betterquesting.name: Grinding [MR]
betterquesting.desc: With a Rock Grinder, you can grind certain materials down into other materials.

betterquesting.name: Basic Alchemy [MR]
betterquesting.desc:
To start off with the alchemical part of Sky Resources, you are going to need to make an Alchemical Fusion Table. With it, you are going to be able to make many different Alchemical items.

 For it to work however, you are going to need a Catalyst sush as Primus Alchemical Dust. Every recipe uses up a certain amount of the Catalyst, represented by the green bar and every Catalyst has a yeild, which determines how much the purple bar gets filled after every recipe, which when full gives you an output.

betterquesting.name: Stone Combustion [MR]
betterquesting.desc: The Stone Casing gives your Combustion Chamber a higher maximum amount of Heat Units and the Stone Combustion Heater lowers the amount of fuel used per Heat Unit, as well as the Heat Units used per recipe, but prevents you from using the Trapdoor.

betterquesting.name: Regular Furnace [MR]
betterquesting.desc: Now that you have Clay and Cobblestone, you can make a regular Furnace with regular efficiency.

betterquesting.name: Clay [MR]
betterquesting.desc: By inserting Water into Dirt, you are able to make Clay or Compressed Clay (by inserting it into Compressed Dirt).

betterquesting.name: Bronze [RM]
betterquesting.desc: Bronze in an alloy of Copper and Tin in a 3-1 ratio.

betterquesting.name: Redstone [MR]
betterquesting.desc: To make Redstone needed for machines and Redstone mechanisms, you are going to need 880 HU, which the Iron Casing allows you to reach.

betterquesting.name: Grass [MR]
betterquesting.desc: To get passive mobs to spawn and to obtain different seeds, you are going to need to make a Grass block.

betterquesting.name: Lava [MR]
betterquesting.desc: Now that you can make Blaze Powder, you can craft it into a block and put it above a Torch to obtain Lava. Melting it could take a few minutes, but if you're lucky, it could even take only a few seconds.

betterquesting.name: Extreme Reactors [PtAL]
betterquesting.desc:
This is everything you need in order to construct the smallest possible Extreme Reactor.

 Extreme Reactors use Yellorium for generating large amounts of power.

betterquesting.name: Sand [MR]
betterquesting.desc: You can grind Gravel to turn it into Sand.

betterquesting.name: Gravel [MR]
betterquesting.desc: You can grind Cobblestone to turn it into Gravel.

betterquesting.name: Condensation [MR]
betterquesting.desc: In order to make Ingots, youare going to need a setup for Condensation. You can see how to make the most basic of setups in the Sky Resources guide. Keep in mind that the bottom block can be any inventory, such as a Chest.

betterquesting.name: Seeds [MR]
betterquesting.desc: By breaking Grass, you can obtain seeds for many different useful crops.

betterquesting.name: Life Infusion [MR]
betterquesting.desc:
Through Life Infusion you can make plants needed for progression, by using health and 2 certain items.

 If you started on the Desert Island, you already have a Sandstone Infusion Stone, but if you didn't, you are going to need to make a Squid farm, which can simply be a pool of Water below y-level 64, make a Dehyndrated Cactus through Combustion and hydrate it with a Water Extractor.

betterquesting.name: Bronze Machines [MR]
betterquesting.desc: Bronze machines are quite efficient and the Combustion Heater uses power instead of fuel.

betterquesting.name: Soul Sand [MR]
betterquesting.desc:
In order to make Glowstone, you are going to first need to make 2 Nether Warts with Spider Eyes, which are mostly player-only drops, through Life Infusion. You can use one of the Nether Warts for making Soul Sand and the other for growing more.

Note: In normal mode, you can use Soul Snad to grow them 4 times faster.

betterquesting.name: Freezer [MR]
betterquesting.desc:
Using a Freezer, you can, well, freeze different materials to turn them into other materials. It's also one of the easiest ways of making Dirt.

 If you started on the Snow Island, you already have this, but if you didn't, you can make Snow through Combustion, shift+right-click on blocks of Snow to duplicate them and craft a Mini Freezer.

betterquesting.name: Let It Go! [MR]
betterquesting.desc: While the Mini Freezer works, it's not really that fast. It's best to make a multiblock Iron Freezer to freezer more things faster.

betterquesting.name: Electrum [RM]
betterquesting.desc: Electrum is an alloy of Silver and Gold.

betterquesting.name: Crucible Inserter [MR]
betterquesting.desc: The Crucible Inserter holds up to a stack of Crystal Shards and automatically throws them in the Crucible when it has room for them, making it so that you don't have to go to it and throw 3 shards in it every few minutes anymore.

betterquesting.name: Combustion Collector [MR]
betterquesting.desc:
The Combustion Collector automatically collects the Combustion recipe outputs, making it so that you don't have to empty it out after every recipe.

 Keep in mind that it cannot be used with a Wooden or Stone Combustion Heater.

betterquesting.name: Quick Dropper [MR]
betterquesting.desc:
Droppers are fine and all, but continuously pressing a Button for getting it to drops items isn't fun. Don't worry though. You can now make a Quick Dropper which doesn't require a Redstone singal (unless you want to turn it off).

 Keep in mind that it cannot be used with a Wooden or Stone Combustion Heater.

betterquesting.name: Hammer Time! [AMM]
betterquesting.desc: The Tinker's Hammer is used for making certain Plates in a 4-1 ratio and for connecting certain Embers blocks.

betterquesting.name: Improved Melting [MR]
betterquesting.desc: The Crucible is used for melting Blaze Powder Blocks into Lava and Crystal Shard into Crystal Fluid. However, you cannot directly collect fluids from it (with a Clay Bucket), so you are going to need a way to pipe them out.

betterquesting.name: Super Hot Combustion [MR]
betterquesting.desc: To reach the amount of Heat Units needed for Glowstone, you are going to need a Netherbrick Casing. Keep in mind that it has really low efficiency, so a fueled Combustion Heater may not be the best idea.

betterquesting.name: Ender Tether [RU]
betterquesting.desc: The Ender Tether has Endermen always teleport to them.

betterquesting.name: Basic Casings [LitF]
betterquesting.desc: The Sturdy Casing is needed for making most Forestry machines and the Reiforced one is needed for making almost all Binnie's Genetics machines.

betterquesting.name: Carpenter [LitF]
betterquesting.desc: The Carpenter uses power, items and a certain fluid to make a certain item.

betterquesting.name: Automatic Squeezing [LitF]
betterquesting.desc: The Squeezer uses power from Squeezing certain items.

betterquesting.name: Pipette [LitF]
betterquesting.desc: The Pipette is a great tool for moving around fluids early on. The great thing about it is that there's not a minimum amount of fluid it can hold.

betterquesting.name: Basic Fluid Storage [T]
betterquesting.desc: The easiest way of storing fluids is in Barrels.

betterquesting.name: Invar [RM]
betterquesting.desc: Invar is an alloy of Iron and Nickel in a 2-1 ratio.

betterquesting.name: Impregnated Materials [LitF]
betterquesting.desc: Now that you have a Carpenter and a Squeezer, you can make Impregnated Casings needed for some Forestry and Binnie's Mods machines and Impregnated Sticks which are mainly needed for starting with Immersive Engineering.

betterquesting.name: Engineer's Arsenal [IT]
betterquesting.desc: To be able to construct all the Multiblock IE machines, you are going to need an Engineer's Hammer and an Engineer's Manual.

betterquesting.name: Coke [IT]
betterquesting.desc: For making Coke Coal and Creosote Oil, you are going to need a Coke Oven.

betterquesting.name: Steel [IT]
betterquesting.desc: For making Steel and starting off with mid-game, you are going to need a multiblock Blast Furnace.

betterquesting.name: Projections [IT]
betterquesting.desc: The Projector allows you to see where everything in an IE multiblock goes in the world, helping you build it.

betterquesting.name: Demon Ingots [UA]
betterquesting.desc: Demon Ingots are obtained by throwing Gold into Lava that's surrounded by Nether Bricks on all sides, besides the top and bottom. Keep in mind that it has a small chance to eat up your Gold without giving you anything.

betterquesting.name: Light Matter Machines [MR]
betterquesting.desc: Light Matter machines are the most efficient Sky Resources machines.

betterquesting.name: Lead Machines [MR]
betterquesting.desc: The Lead Condenser is quite fast and the Lead Combustion Heater uses Radioactive Powder instead of fuel.

betterquesting.name: Brass [RM]
betterquesting.desc: Brass in an alloy of Copper and Zinc in a 3-1 ratio. It can be used for making Casts.

betterquesting.name: Main Gems [MR]
betterquesting.desc: Now that you have Steel, you can make a Cauldron used for cleaning Dirty Gems and possibly getting metals from Crushed Stone and Netherrack. These are the main gems that you are going to need.

betterquesting.name: Secundus [MR]
betterquesting.desc: Secundus Alchemical Dust is the second Catalyst and allows you to get twice the output from your Alchemical Fusion Table, most of the time.

betterquesting.name: Better Steel Production [IT]
betterquesting.desc: You can make a Reinforced Blast Furnace and add Preheaters to it to make it run faster.

betterquesting.name: A Fueled Smeltery [T]
betterquesting.desc: If you for some reason have more Aluminum that Lava, you can make your Smeltey run on Fuel with a Fuel Input Machine.

betterquesting.name: Power From Heat [T]
betterquesting.desc: With the Stirling Engine, you can generate RF from the heat of the molten fluids in Seared Tanks.

betterquesting.name: Basic Alloying [RM]
betterquesting.desc: To make some basic alloys, such as Bronze, you are going to need an Iron Alloy Furnace.

betterquesting.name: Dynamic Trees [CM]
betterquesting.desc: To make just about anything in Integrated Dynamics, you are going to need Menril tree.

betterquesting.name: Grout [T]
betterquesting.desc: To make Grout needed for a Smeltery, you are going to need to construct a multiblock Crusher and use it to crush Coke Coal (on normal or expert mode) or Pulverized Obsidian (on easy mode).

betterquesting.name: Mystical Flowers [VM]
betterquesting.desc:
The Floral Fertilizer, when used on Grass, create Mystical Flowers. To progress through Botania you are going to need all the different Mystical Flowers.

 You only need 1 of every type as you can use Bonemeal on the Petals to grow them into Tall Mysticals Flowers, Shear them and then craft them into 4 Petals.

betterquesting.name: Basic Mana Lenses [VM]
betterquesting.desc: You can add Mana Lenses to Mana Spreaders and Mana Blasters to change how the Mana Bursts that they shoot out behave.

betterquesting.name: Apothecary [VM]
betterquesting.desc: The Petal Apothecary is used for creating Generating and Functional Mana Flowers.

betterquesting.name: The Purest of Daisies [VM]
betterquesting.desc: The Pure Daisy is used mainly for transmuting Wood into Livingwood and Stone into Livingrock.

betterquesting.name: Mana Pool [VM]
betterquesting.desc: The Mana Pool is used for storing Mana and for infusing certain items with it, when they're dropped in it.

betterquesting.name: Mana Spreader [VM]
betterquesting.desc: The Mana Spreader collects Mana from Mana-generating flowers or adjacent Mana Pools and transfers it to the blocks in the direction it is facing.

betterquesting.name: Wand Of The Forest [VM]
betterquesting.desc: The Wand of the Forest is used for configurating Mana-accepting blocks.

betterquesting.name: Basic Mana Generation [VM]
betterquesting.desc: The Endoflame generates Mana from fuel.

betterquesting.name: Mana Items [VM]
betterquesting.desc:
These are all the Mana infused items.

 The main one that you are going to need for progressing through Botania and the pack is Manasteel.

betterquesting.name: Tinker's Tables [T]
betterquesting.desc: To be able to make basic Tinker's Construct Tools, you are going to need a few "Tables".

betterquesting.name: Basic Item Transfer [T]
betterquesting.desc: The easiest way of transferring items is with Wooden Hoppers. However, just like regular Hoppers, they cannot transfer upwards.

betterquesting.name: The Smeltery [T]
betterquesting.desc:
In order to make certain alloys, you are going to need to build a Smeltery.

 You can use the Seared Stone obtained from melting Grout, for casting Seared Bricks and for turning all the Porcelain parts of the Melter into their Seared versions, allowing you to make a basic Smeltery.

betterquesting.name: Smart Casting [T]
betterquesting.desc: For automating the Smeltery, you are going to need a Smart Output. Be careful though, it's really fast.

betterquesting.name: Collecting Blood [CM]
betterquesting.desc: The Blood Extractor is used for collecting Blood by simply having it in your inventory when killing a mob or by shift+right-clicking on Blood on the ground, where a mob took fall damage.

betterquesting.name: Bloody Gems [CM]
betterquesting.desc: By throwing a Dark Gem in a 5-block-pool of Blood, it'll absorb the Blood and turn into a Dark Power Gem.

betterquesting.name: Hardened Blood [CM]
betterquesting.desc: By placing Blood on the ground, it'll soon harden and you'll be able to use a Flint And Steel on it to turn it into Hardened Blood Shards, or you can you can put it in a Drying Basin or a Casting Basin to harden it and them smelt it.

betterquesting.name: Blood Infuser [CM]
betterquesting.desc: The Blood Infuser simply infuses items with Blood.

betterquesting.name: Repairing With Blood [CM]
betterquesting.desc: The Blood Chest uses Blood for repairing items.

betterquesting.name: The Forge [T]
betterquesting.desc: Now that you have Seared Bricks, you can craft a Tool Forge and with it make advanced TIC tools.

betterquesting.name: Promise of Tenacity I [CM]
betterquesting.desc: The Promise of Tenacity I allows your Blood Infuser to hold up to 40 buckets of Blood and unlocks a slot for Promises of Velocity or Productivity.

betterquesting.name: Faster Blood Use [CM]
betterquesting.desc: Promises of Velocity make your Blood Infuser work faster.

betterquesting.name: Less Bloody [CM]
betterquesting.desc: Promises of Productivity decrease the amount of Blood used in recipes in the Blood Infuser.

betterquesting.name: Promise of Tenacity II [CM]
betterquesting.desc: The Promise of Tenacity II allows your Blood Infuser to hold up to 160 buckets of Blood and unlocks a second slot for Promises of Velocity or Productivity.

betterquesting.name: Promise of Tenacity III [CM]
betterquesting.desc: The Promise of Tenacity III allows your Blood Infuser to hold up to 640 buckets of Blood and unlocks a third slot for Promises of Velocity or Productivity.

betterquesting.name: Reviving The Dead [CM]
betterquesting.desc: Blood trees' parts can be squeezed to obtain more Blood than the amount that was used to make them. Keep in mind that the Leaves drop Dead Bushes, so it's best to squeeze them.

betterquesting.name: Flying Like A Witch [CM]
betterquesting.desc: You can costruct a Broom with customizable parts that allows you to fly for the cost of some Blood.

betterquesting.name: Colossal Blood Repairing [CM]
betterquesting.desc: The Clossal Blood Chest is simply a larger Blood Chest.

betterquesting.name: Automated Blood Collection [CM]
betterquesting.desc: The Sanguinary Pedestal automatically collects Blood from the ground. In order for it to collect it from mobs however, you are going to need a Spiked Plate on top of it.

betterquesting.name: The First Calculator [SM]
betterquesting.desc: The basic Calculator is used for msking basic Calculator items.

betterquesting.name: Calculating Atoms [SM]
betterquesting.desc: The Atomic Calculator will allow you to make the Fire Diamonds needed for Empowered Restonia Crystals.

betterquesting.name: Calculations For Scientists [SM]
betterquesting.desc: The Scientific Calculator will allow you to make Restone Ingots, needed for making Pistons, as well as a few other Calculator items.

betterquesting.name: Metal From The Stars [AMM]
betterquesting.desc: Link the Floating Crystal to Iron Ore to turn it into Starmetal Ore.

betterquesting.name: Rubbery Goodness [RM]
betterquesting.desc:
For making Tech Reborn Cables, you are going to need Rubber.

 To make Rubber, you are going to need to grow a Rubber Trees, collect the Sap that shows up on its Logs from time to time with a Treetap, and smelt it.

betterquesting.name: Advancing [RM]
betterquesting.desc: Advanced Circuits are needed for making more advanced machines in certain mods.

betterquesting.name: Not So Basic [RM]
betterquesting.desc: The Basic Machine Frame is needed for making the simplest of Tech Reborn machines.

betterquesting.name: You See Me Rolling [RM]
betterquesting.desc:
The Rolling Machine is used for making certain metal items needed for progression.

 In expert mode, this includes Buckets.

betterquesting.name: More Sap! [RM]
betterquesting.desc: For getting Rubber from every part of a Rubber tree, extracting Fluids from Cell and a fww other things, you are going to need an Extractor.

betterquesting.name: Compression [RM]
betterquesting.desc: The Compressor is used for making Plates with power.

betterquesting.name: Powered Alloying [RM]
betterquesting.desc: The Alloy Smelter is a powered Iron Allow Furnace.

betterquesting.name: Automatic Cleaning [MR]
betterquesting.desc: The Rock Cleaner uses Water and Power to automatically clean Dirty Gems and Crushed Stone and Netherrack.

betterquesting.name: You're Crushing It! [MR]
betterquesting.desc: The Rock Crusher uses power to automatically grind materials and has a 3 times higher chance for giving outputs.

betterquesting.name: Automating Water [MR]
betterquesting.desc: With the Aqueous Concentrator you can automatically insert Water and with the Aqueous Deconcentrator you can automatically extract Water.

betterquesting.name: Ember [AMM]
betterquesting.desc: By piping Ember Shards or Crystals in an Ember Activator, you can turn them into raw Ember energy.

betterquesting.name: Master Smelting [TM]
betterquesting.desc: The Induction Smelter allows you to get some extra items from smelting.

betterquesting.name: Alloying With Ember [AMM]
betterquesting.desc: The Mixer Centrifuge uses Ember to mix 2 different molten metals and make alloys.

betterquesting.name: Stamping With Ember [AMM]
betterquesting.desc: The Stamper uses Ember and Stamps to shape molten metals.

betterquesting.name: Powered Melting [TM]
betterquesting.desc: The Magma Crucible uses power to melt certain items.

betterquesting.name: Manyullyn [T]
betterquesting.desc: Manyullyn is an alloy of Cobalt and Ardite.

betterquesting.name: Ash [AMM]
betterquesting.desc: The Cinder Plinth uses Ember to turn mundane materials into Ash.

betterquesting.name: Firin' My Laser! [AMM]
betterquesting.desc: The Beam Cannon usses Ember to fire a beam that can either kill a line of mobs or activate an Exchange Tablet.

betterquesting.name: Metallurgic Infusion [IM]
betterquesting.desc: The Metallurgic Infuser is used for making all the different Alloys needed for crafting all the different Mekanism machines.

betterquesting.name: Latex From Trees [IM]
betterquesting.desc: The Latex Fluid Extractor collects Latex from trees, slowly breaking them in the process.

betterquesting.name: Osgloglas [T]
betterquesting.desc: Osgloglas is an alloy of all the Mekanism ingots.

betterquesting.name: HOP Graphite [IT]
betterquesting.desc: To make HOP Graphite, mainly needed for making Empowered Void Crystals, you are going to need a multiblock Squeezer.

betterquesting.name: Peat [LitF]
betterquesting.desc: By putting Bog Earth around Water, it'll slowly turn into Peat. Peat can be used as a fuel or it can be smelted into Ash.

betterquesting.name: Shaving Trees [T]
betterquesting.desc: You can use Clay to make Clay Shears, used for harvesting Leaves, which in return allow you to make more Plant Matter and more Clay.

betterquesting.name: Basic Fluid Transfer [T]
betterquesting.desc: The easiest way of transferring fluids is with Faucets and Channels. They cannot however transfer upwards.

betterquesting.name: Basic Melting [T]
betterquesting.desc: To be able to melt different materials, you are going to need a Porcelain Melter and Porcelain Tank filled with Lava or a Porcelain Heater filled with fuel below it.

betterquesting.name: Basic Casting [T]
betterquesting.desc: To be able to cast different items, you are going to need a Porcelain Casting Table and a Porcelain Casting Basin.

betterquesting.name: Iron Casing [UA]
betterquesting.desc: The Iron Casing is needed for crafting most AA machines.

betterquesting.name: Wood Casing [UA]
betterquesting.desc: The Wood Casing is the first one in the "Casing progression line" and is also needed for a few AA blocks.

betterquesting.name: Devices [TM]
betterquesting.desc: The Device Frame is needed for crafting TE devices.

betterquesting.name: Machines [TM]
betterquesting.desc: The Machine Frame is needed for crafting TE machines.

betterquesting.name: The Basic Crystals [IM]
betterquesting.desc: You are going to need to make Crystals to progress through the pack.

betterquesting.name: Advanced Frames [RM]
betterquesting.desc: The Advanced Machine Frame is needed for making the most advanced Tech Reborn machines.

betterquesting.name: Chemical Reactions [RM]
betterquesting.desc: The Chemical Reactor combines 2 different types of items.

betterquesting.name: Industrial Blast Furnace [RM]
betterquesting.desc: To make Tungstensteel, needed for making Dark Matter, you are going to need a multiblock Industrial Blast Furnace with at least 3000 Heat. Keep in mind that you need to fill the multiblock with Lava.

betterquesting.name: Tungstensteel [RM]
betterquesting.desc: You can turn the Hot Tungstensteel into regular Tungstensteel by putting it in a Vacuum Freezer or in a Fluid Transposer with Cryotheum.

betterquesting.name: A Cleaner Inventory [RM]
betterquesting.desc: The Recyler turns items into Scrap.

betterquesting.name: UU-Matter [RM]
betterquesting.desc: Have you ever wanted to make Clay that can be shaped into any vanilla or TR item? Well now you can!

betterquesting.name: Nuclear Fusion [RM]
betterquesting.desc: For making certain TR materials, as well as Blutonium, you are going to need a multiblock Fusion Reactor.

betterquesting.name: Implossion Compression [RM]
betterquesting.desc: To turn certain Gem Dusts into Gems and Iridium Alloy Ingot into Plates, you are going to need an Implosion Compressor.

betterquesting.name: Litherite [ET]
betterquesting.desc:
Litherite is needed for making Tier 1 ET machines.

 Left-click with the Assembler on a multiblock Controller to see all the required blocks for the multiblock, right-click to construct it and shift+right-click to pick it up.

betterquesting.name: Alabaster [ET]
betterquesting.desc: Alabaster can be obtained with a Tier 1 Void Resource Miner and is one of the materials needed for making Dark Matter. Keep in mind that it has the same multiblock structure as the Tier 1 Void Ore Miner.

betterquesting.name: Mica [ET]
betterquesting.desc: Mica can be obtained with a Tier 2 Void Resource Miner and is mainly used for crafting Modifiers for the ET multiblock machines.

betterquesting.name: Graphite [PtAL]
betterquesting.desc: To make Graphite needed for the different Reactors, you are going to need a Manufactory.

betterquesting.name: Extra Ore Drops [PtAL]
betterquesting.desc: To craft certain machines from NuclearCraft, you are going to need extra materials that drop from certain Ores.

betterquesting.name: Burning With Radiation [PtAL]
betterquesting.desc: The Nuclear Furnace uses radioactive materials for smelting instead of fuel.

betterquesting.name: Cool! [PtAL]
betterquesting.desc: For your Fission Reactor to work, you are going to need to keep it at a decent temperature. For that, you are going to need Coolers.

betterquesting.name: Lemme Smash! [IT]
betterquesting.desc: For making your first Plates, you are going to need an Iron Hammer and a Crushing Table. Simply put an Ingot on the Crushing Table and hit it with the Hammer to turn it into a Plate. Keep in mind that it doesn't work with all metals and especially not with alloys.

betterquesting.name: Cyanite [PtAL]
betterquesting.desc: Cyanite is a byproduct of burning Yellorium.

betterquesting.name: Ludicrite [PtAL]
betterquesting.desc: Ludicrite is one of the materials needed for making Dark Matter.

betterquesting.name: Enderium Machines [MR]
betterquesting.desc: Enderium machines are better than rest of the machines, besides the Dark and White Matter ones.

betterquesting.name: The Wither [MR]
betterquesting.desc: Find a way to make Wither Skeletons and kill the Wither.

betterquesting.name: Dark Matter Machines [MR]
betterquesting.desc: Dark Matter machines have the highest max heat and best speed, but use Dark Matter to function.

betterquesting.name: Antimony [AMM]
betterquesting.desc:
Antimony can be used as a replacement for Emeralds in Villager Trades.

 To make it, you need to add an Alchemical Recombulator on top of a Mixer Centrifuge and you do everything that you do when making an item in a Exchange Tablet, but this time instead using and making items, you're using and making fluids, well, there still are the Ash Piles.

betterquesting.name: Iridium [MR]
betterquesting.desc: You can make your first Iridium by processing Platinum Ore in an Induction Smelter.

betterquesting.name: The End? [MR]
betterquesting.desc: You now have everything needed for going to the End and killing the Ender Dragon, but that's not really the end of the pack, is it?

betterquesting.name: Charger [DS]
betterquesting.desc: Instead of making Charged Certus Quartz Crystals through Combustion, you can simply make them with a Charger.

betterquesting.name: The Purest Of Crystals [DS]
betterquesting.desc: To make many things in AE2, you are going to need Pure Crystals, Just drop the Seeds in Water and they'll slowly grow.

betterquesting.name: Faster Crystal Growth [DS]
betterquesting.desc: To grow Crystal Seeds faster, you can make a Crystal Growth Chamber and put them in it.

betterquesting.name: Lightning Up Diamonds [SM]
betterquesting.desc: The Conductor Mast uses Lightning to generate power and turn Fire Diamonds into Electric Diamonds.

betterquesting.name: Flawless Calculations [SM]
betterquesting.desc: The Flawless Calculator allows you to make some more complex vanilla and Calculator items.

betterquesting.name: Hunger From Trees [SM]
betterquesting.desc: The Hunger Processor store hunger points and the Hunger Module slowly regenerates your hunger when it's in your inventory.

betterquesting.name: Health From Trees [SM]
betterquesting.desc: The Health Processor store health points and the Health Module slowly regenerates your health when it's in your inventory.

betterquesting.name: Collecting Items From Trees [SM]
betterquesting.desc: The Algorithm Assimilator automatically harvests Pear and Diamond Saplings.

betterquesting.name: Collecting Points From Trees [SM]
betterquesting.desc: The Stone Assimilator automatically collects health and hunger from Amethyst and Tanzanite trees.

betterquesting.name: Imbuing Station [RU]
betterquesting.desc: Vines can be obtained from huge Jungle Trees and Lily Pads can be obtained from fishing.

betterquesting.name: Apiary [LitF]
betterquesting.desc: The Apiary allows Bees to breed and create their products.

betterquesting.name: Feeling Moist [LitF]
betterquesting.desc: The Moistener uses Water, Wheat and another item for making certain blocks.

betterquesting.name: Attracting Bees [LitF]
betterquesting.desc: The Bee Attractor uses power and Seed Oil for attracting Bees.

betterquesting.name: The Centrifuge [LitF]
betterquesting.desc: The Centrifuge is mainly used for processing Bee Combs into useful items.

betterquesting.name: A Better Home For Bees [LitF]
betterquesting.desc: The Bee House is better than the Apiary, but cannot be automated.

betterquesting.name: Resonator [UA]
betterquesting.desc: The Resonator makes certain items, provided that you have enough GP.

betterquesting.name: All The GP! [UA]
betterquesting.desc: The Dragon Egg Mill generates a large amount of GP when there's a Dragon Egg on top of it.

betterquesting.name: ExU Upgrades [UA]
betterquesting.desc: You can make Upgrades for your ExU machines and Transfer Nodes. They do however increase the amount of GP needed for them to work.

betterquesting.name: Reinforced Upgrade Kit [TM]
betterquesting.desc: Reinforced Upgrade Kits allow you to upgrade your TE machines from Hardened to Reinforced Tier.

betterquesting.name: Signalum Upgrade Kit [TM]
betterquesting.desc: Signalum Upgrade Kits allow you to upgrade your TE machines from Reinforced to Signalum Tier.

betterquesting.name: Resonant Upgrade Kit [TM]
betterquesting.desc: Resonant Upgrade Kits allow you to upgrade your TE machines from Signalum to Resonant Tier.

betterquesting.name: Hardened Upgrade Kit [TM]
betterquesting.desc: Hardned Upgrade Kits allow you to upgrade your TE machines from Basic to Hardened Tier.

betterquesting.name: Aluminum Brass [T]
betterquesting.desc: Aluminum Brass is an alloy of Aluminum and Copper in a 3-1 ratio. It can be ued for making Casts.

betterquesting.name: Compressed Redstone [IM]
betterquesting.desc: Compressed Redstone counts as 80 Redstone in the Metallurgic Infuser.

betterquesting.name: Compressed Diamond [IM]
betterquesting.desc: The Compressed Diamond counts as 80 Diamond in the Metallurgic Infuser.

betterquesting.name: Compressed Obsidian [IM]
betterquesting.desc: Compressed Obsidian counts as 80 Obsidian in the Metallurgic Infuser.

betterquesting.name: Advanced Factory [IM]
betterquesting.desc: The Advanced Tier Installer upgrades your Basic Factories to Advanced Factories.

betterquesting.name: Ultimate Factory [IM]
betterquesting.desc: The Ultimate Tier Installer upgrades certain Elite blocks to their Ultimate versions.

betterquesting.name: Basic Factory [IM]
betterquesting.desc: The Basic Tier Installer turns your regular Mekanism machines into Basic Factories.

betterquesting.name: Elite Factory [IM]
betterquesting.desc: The Elite Tier Installer upgrades your Advanced Factories to Elite Factories.

betterquesting.name: Compressed Carbon [IM]
betterquesting.desc: Compressed Carbon counts as 80 Carbon in the Metallurgic Infuser.

betterquesting.name: Honey! [LitF]
betterquesting.desc: One of the most common Bee products is Honey.

betterquesting.name: Wax [LitF]
betterquesting.desc: Different Bee species gives different types of Wax.

betterquesting.name: A True Beekeeper [LitF]
betterquesting.desc: The Apiarist's set allows you to get close to Bees that would normally hurt you.

betterquesting.name: Analysing...     [LitF]
betterquesting.desc: The Portable Analyzer gives you more information about whatever you're analyzing, provided that you have Honey Drops in it.

betterquesting.name: Silky Smooth [T]
betterquesting.desc: Silky Jewels can be added to your tools to give them Sick Touch.

betterquesting.name: Osmiridium [T]
betterquesting.desc: Osmiridium is an alloy of Osmium and Iridium.

betterquesting.name: Liquid Starlight [AMM]
betterquesting.desc: The Lightwell turns certain materials into Liquid Starlight, Water and Lava.

betterquesting.name: Luminous Crafting Table [AMM]
betterquesting.desc: To make a Luminous Crafting Table and a Resonating Wand, link the Floating Crystal to a Crafting Table and use the recipe in the Journal.

betterquesting.name: Going Wireless [DS]
betterquesting.desc:
Now that you have a Security Terminal, you can add a Wireless Access Point to your ME system, craft a Wireless Crafting Terminal, craft that together with a regular Fluid and Gas Terminal to turn it into a Unviersal Wireless Terminal and put it in the top right slot of the Security Terminal to link it to your ME system.

 You can switch between its modes by shift+right-clicking.

betterquesting.name: Freezeing In A Vacuum [RM]
betterquesting.desc: The multiblock Vacuum Freezer allows you to freeze certain items. That's about all it can do.

betterquesting.name: Industrial Centrifuge [RM]
betterquesting.desc: The Industrial Centrifuge is used for turning certain items into their basic components, just like every other Centrifuge in this pack.

betterquesting.name: Industrial Grinding [RM]
betterquesting.desc: Note: Water goes in the middle.

betterquesting.name: Engineer's Workbench [IT]
betterquesting.desc: For making certain parts and making some craftable parts cheaper, you are going to need an Engineer's Workbench.

betterquesting.name: Runic Altar [VM]
betterquesting.desc: The Runic Altar is used for creating Runes.

betterquesting.name: CAD [VM]
betterquesting.desc: To start off with Psi, you are going to need to construct a basic CAD.

betterquesting.name: Casting Spells [VM]
betterquesting.desc: To make different Spells you are going to need a Spell Programmers and to cast them you are going to need to put them on a Spell Bullet, select in on your CAD and fire it.

betterquesting.name: Tool AoE [T]
betterquesting.desc: You can add Expanders to your tools to make them mine in a larger area.

betterquesting.name: Mending Moss [T]
betterquesting.desc: By using Moss on a Bookshelf, you can turn it into Mending Moss, which when added to your tools will slowly repair them.

betterquesting.name: Reinforcement [T]
betterquesting.desc: To reinforce your tools or even make them unbreakable, you are going to need Reinforcements.

betterquesting.name: Drying Racks [T]
betterquesting.desc: Drying Racks allow you to dry certain items into Jerkies, Leather and some other things.

betterquesting.name: Hot Wood [T]
betterquesting.desc: With Firewood you can make tools that smelt smeltable blocks that you break with them.

betterquesting.name: Smite [T]
betterquesting.desc: You can add Consecrated Soil to your tools to add Smite to them.

betterquesting.name: Clay Armor [T]
betterquesting.desc: The earliest armor you can make is Clay Armor.

betterquesting.name: Speedy Mana Transferring [VM]
betterquesting.desc: Sparks are used for quickly transferring Mana between Mana-accepting blocks.

betterquesting.name: Portal To The Alfheim [VM]
betterquesting.desc:
The Portal of the Afheim will allow you to transmute Mana infused items into their Elven versions.

 Note: To complete this quest, you need to have everything in your inventory at the same time.

betterquesting.name: Elven Items [VM]
betterquesting.desc: These are all the Elven items.

betterquesting.name: The Gaia Guardian [VM]
betterquesting.desc: You can obtain a Gaia Spirit by summoning the Gaia Guardian with the structure shown in the Lexica and killing him.

betterquesting.name: All The Relics [VM]
betterquesting.desc: You get a Dice of Fate from killing a Gaia Guardian. You can then roll it to collect a certain relic. Your goal is simple: collect all the relics.

betterquesting.name: Pink Withers! [VM]
betterquesting.desc: The Pinkinator can be dropped by a Gaia Guardian and allows you to make Withers pink and friendly.

betterquesting.name: Botanical Brewery [VM]
betterquesting.desc: The Botania Brewery allows you to make certain potions using Mana that can be consumed more than once.

betterquesting.name: Morphing Tool [VM]
betterquesting.desc: The Morphing Tool store modded Wrenches and Hammers.

betterquesting.name: Akashic Tome [VM]
betterquesting.desc: The Akashic Tome stores modded guides.

betterquesting.name: Mirion [T]
betterquesting.desc: Mirion is an alloy of all the Botania ingots, Cobalt and Glass.

betterquesting.name: Bonsai Pots [RU]
betterquesting.desc: Hopping Bonsai Pots are one-block automatic tree farms that always keep a Sapling.

betterquesting.name: Automating Cobblestone [RU]
betterquesting.desc: Now that you have Redstone, you can craft a Block Breaker which automatically breaks Cobblestone for you and puts it in an inventory behind it.

betterquesting.name: Playing With Vectors I [RU]
betterquesting.desc: Vector Plates move mobs and allow them to spawn on them.

betterquesting.name: Killing Ghosts [RU]
betterquesting.desc: Ectoplasm can be obtained by killing the small Spirits that a occasionally spawn after killing a mob with potions or other magical items.

betterquesting.name: Energy Battery [CM]
betterquesting.desc: For your ID system to work, you are going to need to connect an Energy Battery to it.

betterquesting.name: Interacting With The World [CM]
betterquesting.desc: Integrated Tunnels allows you to use the read information for more complex interaction with the world.

betterquesting.name: Reading And Sending Information [CM]
betterquesting.desc: Integrated Dynamics is a mod used for reading and writing information in the world.

betterquesting.name: Playing Around With Variables [CM]
betterquesting.desc: You could also make Variables so that certain things are written only when specific things are read.

betterquesting.name: Collecting Spirits [CM]
betterquesting.desc: By killing a mob with a Vengeance Ring equipped, its Spirit will stick around for a while. You can then use a Vengeance Focus to lure it to a Box of Eternal Closure and capture it.

betterquesting.name: Killing Spirits [CM]
betterquesting.desc: You can use a Piercing Vengenace Focus to kill Vengeance Spirits.

betterquesting.name: Reantimating The Dead [CM]
betterquesting.desc: The Spirit Reanimator makes the Spawn Egg of that mob that has its Spirit in the Box of Eternal Closure in it.

betterquesting.name: Generating Mob Drops [CM]
betterquesting.desc: The Spirit Furnace generates the drops of the mob that has its Spirit in the Box Of Iternal Closure in it, using Blood.

betterquesting.name: Structured Crafting [CM]
betterquesting.desc: By putting blocks in a 3x3 area behind the Structured Crafter and applying a Redstone signal to it, whatever those blocks in that shape would make in a crafting grid will come out the front of it.

betterquesting.name: Cabality Proxies [CM]
betterquesting.desc: Capabily Proxies allow you to access tile entites from a distance.

betterquesting.name: Elemental Rods [VM]
betterquesting.desc: These are easiest Rods you can make. Just like all the other Rods from Botania, they use Mana to do a certain thing.

betterquesting.name: Psionic Armor And Tools [VM]
betterquesting.desc: With Psimetal and Psigems, you can make tools and armor with which you can cast spells.

betterquesting.name: Redstone Arsenal [TM]
betterquesting.desc: Redstone Arsenal is a mod that adds in Fluxed armor and tools that have special abilities, activated by pressing "V".

betterquesting.name: Using Fluids [TM]
betterquesting.desc: The Fluid Transposer allows you to fill Tanks and other blocks and items that can store fluids and allows you to make certain items with fluids.

betterquesting.name: Infusing With Power [TM]
betterquesting.desc: The Energetic Infuser allows you to recharge your powered items and make some Fluxed items.

betterquesting.name: Automatic Fishing [TM]
betterquesting.desc: The Aquatic Entangler uses Aqua-Chow, when it Water to fish out some Fish.

betterquesting.name: Growing With Power [TM]
betterquesting.desc: The Phytogenic Insolator uses Fertilizers and power to grow crops faster and more efficiently.

betterquesting.name: Speeding Up By Cooling [TM]
betterquesting.desc: The Thermal Mediator uses coolants to speed up adjacent TE machines.

betterquesting.name: Extracting From Trees [TM]
betterquesting.desc: The Arboreal Extractor collects fluids from trees. Dark Oak trees give Sap and all other vanilla trees give Resin, with Spruce being the fastest.

betterquesting.name: Osmium Compressor [IM]
betterquesting.desc: The Osmium Compressor is used for making alloys with Osmium.

betterquesting.name: The Boiler [IM]
betterquesting.desc:
The Boiler is a multiblock that generates Steam.


 These here are the materials needed for the smallest one.

betterquesting.name: The Turbine [IM]
betterquesting.desc:
The Turbine is a multiblock that Generates power from Steam.
 
 These are all the materials needed for the smallest possible Turbine.

betterquesting.name: Transfer Pipes [UA]
betterquesting.desc: One way of transferring around items is with Transfer Pipes.

betterquesting.name: Disenchanting With Blood [CM]
betterquesting.desc: The Purifier uses Blood to transfer the enchantments of your tools onto a Blook.

betterquesting.name: Quantum Physics With Blood [CM]
betterquesting.desc: Entangled Chalices hold the same fluid.

betterquesting.name: A Satchel And Crafting Table On A Stick In One [CM]
betterquesting.desc: Note: Crafting Tasks don't detect crafting in it.

betterquesting.name: Automated Calculations [SM]
betterquesting.desc: The Docking Station allows you to automate Calculators.

betterquesting.name: Frame-By-Frame [TM]
betterquesting.desc: Funky Locomotion is a mod that allows you to move around Frames and different blocks connected to them.

betterquesting.name: Miniaturization [RU]
betterquesting.desc: 4 Miniaturization Field Projectors can create a field that allows you to make certain items from the blocks placed in the field, when a certain item is thrown in it.

betterquesting.name: Tunneling [RU]
betterquesting.desc: Tunnels allow you to connect your Compact Machines with the outside world.

betterquesting.name: Your Own Room [RU]
betterquesting.desc: The Spectre Key gives you your own room in the Spectre Dimension.

betterquesting.name: Custom Dimlets [RT]
betterquesting.desc: Using the Dimlet Worktable, you can deconstruct and create new Dimlets.

betterquesting.name: Infusing Machines [RT]
betterquesting.desc: The Machine Infuser infuses RFTools machines with Dimensional Shards, making them better in a certain way.

betterquesting.name: Universal Cables [RT]
betterquesting.desc: XNet adds cables which can transfer items, fluids and power at the same time, that aren't tile entities, therefore don't lag servers.

betterquesting.name: Prosperity Shards [MC]
betterquesting.desc: Prosperity Shards can only be obtained from their ores and are needed for making all the different resource seeds.

betterquesting.name: Inferium Smelting [MC]
betterquesting.desc: You can use Inferium to make a more efficient Furnace and Coal.

betterquesting.name: Seed Processing [MC]
betterquesting.desc: The Seed Reprocessor turns resource seeds into their corresponding Essence.

betterquesting.name: Assembling Carts [RM]
betterquesting.desc: The Cart Assembler is needed for making Carts.

betterquesting.name: Questing Ram Quest [E]
betterquesting.desc: All you need to do for this Throphy is to find a Questing Ram and give it Wool of every color.

betterquesting.name: Flux [SM]
betterquesting.desc: Flux is obtained by throwing Redstone into Lava.

betterquesting.name: Going Completely Wireless [SM]
betterquesting.desc: Flux Networks allows you to make your own wireless RF network that you can insert or extract power from.

betterquesting.name: Obtaining Circuits [SM]
betterquesting.desc: The Precision Chamber creates Dirty Circuits from Dirt and Damaged Circuits from Stone.

betterquesting.name: Repairing Circuits [SM]
betterquesting.desc: The Restoration and Reassembly Chamber allow you to repair Dirty and Damaged Circuits.

betterquesting.name: Applying Advanced Modules [SM]
betterquesting.desc: The Module Workbench allows you to add Modules to the Flawless Calculator.

betterquesting.name: Using Circuits [SM]
betterquesting.desc: The Fabrication Chamber uses Circuits from an adjacent Storage Chamber to easily make certain items.

betterquesting.name: Automatic Anviling [AMM]
betterquesting.desc: The Dawnstone Anvil, in combination with the Automatic Hammer, can automatically deconstruct or repair your tools with different materials.

betterquesting.name: Analysing Circuits [SM]
betterquesting.desc: The Analysing Chamber analyses Circuits and has a chance to give you certain items in the process.

betterquesting.name: Starlight Infuser [AMM]
betterquesting.desc: The Starlight Infuser multiblocks allows you to transmute certain items with a 1/3 chance of using up a block of Liquid Starlight.

betterquesting.name: Regular Gems [AMM]
betterquesting.desc: Regular Gems are all the Gems obtained from Stone.

betterquesting.name: Dark Gems [AMM]
betterquesting.desc: Dark Gems are all the Gems obtained from Netherrack.

betterquesting.name: Light Gems [AMM]
betterquesting.desc: Light Gems are all the Gems obtained from End Stone.

betterquesting.name: Grading Materials [AMM]
betterquesting.desc: With the Material Grader you have a chance to increase a material's stats.

betterquesting.name: Collecting Chaos [AMM]
betterquesting.desc: Passive Chaos Pylons passivly generate Chaos over time, while Burner Chaos Pylons use fuel to generate Chaos.

betterquesting.name: Chaos Altar [AMM]
betterquesting.desc: The Chaos Altar collects Chaos and uses it for either charging Chaos items or transmuting items.

betterquesting.name: Storing Chaos [AMM]
betterquesting.desc: The Chaos Orb stores Chaos and automatically charges your Chaos items.

betterquesting.name: Glowing Roses [AMM]
betterquesting.desc: Glow Roses are simply Roses that glow. Why not have them all?

betterquesting.name: Moving Nodes [AMM]
betterquesting.desc: You can craft a Chaos Node Mover to move Chaos Nodes (those glowing white orbs scattered around the world).

betterquesting.name: Rainbow Generator [UA]
betterquesting.desc: The Rainbow Generator generates large amounts of power when all the other generators are running at the same time.

betterquesting.name: Legal Chunk Loading [UA]
betterquesting.desc: For this you are going to need to make a Villager farm, find one that will accept the Contract, put him in a Golden Lasso and use it to craft a Chunk Loading Ward which loads a 3x3 area of chunks

betterquesting.name: Wooden Spikes [UA]
betterquesting.desc: Wooden Spikes damage mobs until they get to half a heart.

betterquesting.name: Stone Spikes [UA]
betterquesting.desc: Stone Spikes damage mobs and kill them.

betterquesting.name: Golden Spikes [UA]
betterquesting.desc: Golden Spikes damage mobs and make them drop experience.

betterquesting.name: Diamond Spikes [UA]
betterquesting.desc: Diamond Spikes damage mobs and make them drop player-only drops.

betterquesting.name: Fermenting [LitF]
betterquesting.desc: The Fermenter uses power, items and a fluid to create a different fluid.

betterquesting.name: But Still! [LitF]
betterquesting.desc: The Still uses power to turn one fluid into another fluid.

betterquesting.name: Worms [UA]
betterquesting.desc: You can obtain Worms by tilling Grass blocks. What they do is they always keep a 3x3 area of dirt below them tilled and hydrated.

betterquesting.name: A Different Type Of Coal [UA]
betterquesting.desc: By putting Canola Seeds in a Composter it'll turn into Biomass, which you can then smelt to turn it into Biocoal.

betterquesting.name: Multiblock Auto-Craafting [DS]
betterquesting.desc: This is everything needed for the smallest possible multiblock.

betterquesting.name: Basic Craftimg Table [O]
betterquesting.desc: The Basic Crafting Table is a Crafting Table with a 3x3 grid, but can be used for crafting only one item.

betterquesting.name: Advanced Crafting Table [O]
betterquesting.desc: The Advanced Crafting Table is a Crafting Table with a 5x5 grid.

betterquesting.name: Elite Crafting Table [O]
betterquesting.desc: The Elite Crafting Table is a Crafting Table with a 7x7 grid.

betterquesting.name: Ultimate Crafting Table [O]
betterquesting.desc: The Ultimate Crafting Table is a Crafting Table with a 9x9 grid.

betterquesting.name: Combination Crafting [O]
betterquesting.desc: You can make certain Extended Crafting items and quickly make Empowered Crystals by putting the required items on a Crafting Core with Pedestals around it and supplying it with power.

betterquesting.name: Quantum Compression [O]
betterquesting.desc: The Quantum Compressor, with 500MRF and an Ultimate Crafting Catalyst, can turn 100K Ingots of a certain type into the corresponding Singularity.

betterquesting.name: The Ultimate Ingot [O]
betterquesting.desc: To make any creative item, you are going to need Ultimate Ingots.

betterquesting.name: Creative Fluid Storage Disk [O]
betterquesting.desc: The Creative Fluid Storage Disk can hold an infinite amount of fluids, but as the Quantum Fluid Disk does the same, it's mainly used for crafting.

betterquesting.name: Creative Blood Orb [O]
betterquesting.desc: The Creative Blood Orb gives you endless amounts of Blood, making the creation of Empowered Restonia Crystals much easier.

betterquesting.name: Creative Storage Disk [O]
betterquesting.desc: The Creative Storage Disk can hold an infinite amount of items, but as the Quantum Storage Disk does the same, it's mainly used for crafting.

betterquesting.name: Creative Exchanger [O]
betterquesting.desc: The Creative Exchanger allows you to make endless amounts of any block.

betterquesting.name: Creative Vending Upgrade [O]
betterquesting.desc: This is your goal in that pack, the final creative item. Will you manage to craft it?

betterquesting.name: Shaping Glass [LitF]
betterquesting.desc: The Thermionic Fabricator uses Molten Glass and items for making Electron Tubes and other Glass items.

betterquesting.name: Circuits With Upgrades [LitF]
betterquesting.desc: Using a Soldering Iron, you can add Electron Tubes to Circuits, which you can then add to your Forestry machines to upgrade them.

betterquesting.name: Grafter [LitF]
betterquesting.desc: The Grafter has a 100 percent chance of giving you Saplings from Leaves.

betterquesting.name: Databases [LitF]
betterquesting.desc: Databases store information about the regular version of whatever you're analyzing.

betterquesting.name: The Alveary [LitF]
betterquesting.desc: The Alveary is a much better multiblock version of the Apiary that you can add different parts to in order to acommodate the many different species of Bees as well as for collecting Larvae.

betterquesting.name: Everything Needed For Messing With Genes [LitF]
Automatable Apiary [LitF]
betterquesting.desc: The Industrial Apiary is an upgradable powered Apiary.

betterquesting.name: Forced Mutations [LitF]
betterquesting.desc: The Mutagen Producer creates Mutagen from Redstone, Glowstone, Uranium and Yellorium and can be used in the Mutatron and Advanced Mutatron for breeding bees without any special requires, but yet with a small chance of killing the Bees.

betterquesting.name: Constantan [IT]
betterquesting.desc: To make Constantan, you are going to need to mix Copper and Nickel in a multiblock Alloy Kiln. It's not that useful of a material, but still.

betterquesting.name: Using Kinetic Energy [IT]
betterquesting.desc: Water Wheels generate a set amount of power determined by how much Water is flowing over them and Windmills generate a set amount of power determined by the weather and how high they are.

betterquesting.name: Using All The Wind [IT]
betterquesting.desc: You can add Windmill Sails to your Windmills to make them generate more power.

betterquesting.name: The Cloche [IT]
betterquesting.desc: The Garden Cloche uses power and Water to grow crops faster.

betterquesting.name: Biodiesel [IT]
betterquesting.desc: By combining Ethanol, made in a Fermenter and Plant Oil, made in a Squeezer, in a Refinery, you can make Biodiesel.

betterquesting.name: Void Samples [IT]
betterquesting.desc: Core Sample Drills give you information about the resources in your chunk.

betterquesting.name: Collecting Oil [IT]
betterquesting.desc: By putting a Pumpjack in a chunk that has Oil, it'll start slowly collecting it.

betterquesting.name: Diesel [IT]
betterquesting.desc: By putting Oil in a Distillation Tower, it'll turn into Diesel and you'll get Bitumen as a byproduct.

betterquesting.name: Lubricant [IT]
betterquesting.desc: Lubrican is used for speeding up certain IE multiblocks.

betterquesting.name: Mixing It Up! [IT]
betterquesting.desc: The Mixer allows you to mix certain fluids and items for making other fluids.

betterquesting.name: Distilling Water [IT]
betterquesting.desc: The multiblock Distillery distills Water and makes Salt in the process.

betterquesting.name: Leaving Food For The Animals [IT]
betterquesting.desc: Instead of manually feeding animals, you can leave them food in the Feeding Trough and they'll eat it from time to time.

betterquesting.name: Generating Electricity [IT]
betterquesting.desc: The Thermopile generates Electricity by having Water or Ice and Lava around it.

betterquesting.name: Gardens [AMC]
betterquesting.desc:
Gardens, when broken, give you different plants.

 Note: The Leaves that you grind must be from a tree i.e. they mustn't be broken and placed.

betterquesting.name: The Market [AMC]
betterquesting.desc: The Market allows you to trade in Emeralds for crops and other HarvestCraft items.

betterquesting.name: Tofu [AMC]
betterquesting.desc: Instead of making a passive mob farm, you could grow Soybeans, turn them into Tofu and use that instead of meat in most recipes.

betterquesting.name: Cooking Utensils [AMC]
betterquesting.desc: You earn a heart for every 50 different foods you eat, so you are going to want to make as many different foods as possible. To achieve that however, you are going to need some basic cooking utensils.

betterquesting.name: Epic Bacon [AMC]
betterquesting.desc: Epic Bacon gives a lot of saturation.

betterquesting.name: Sand Generator [AMD]
betterquesting.desc: With Liquid Starlight and Lava you could make a Sand generator, which drops Aquamarine Shale from time to time.

betterquesting.name: Dungeon Map [E]
betterquesting.desc:
To enter The Twilight Forest, you are going to need to make a 2x2 body of Water, surround it with Grass, put flowers on the Grass, throw a Dragonstone in the Water and jump in!

 The Twilight Forest is a dimension filled with dungeons and bosses, so obviously the first thing you need to do there is crafting a Dungeon Map.

betterquesting.name: The Naga [E]
betterquesting.desc: To obtain this Throphy you are going to need to find a Naga Courtyard and kill the Naga.

betterquesting.name: Twilight Lich [E]
betterquesting.desc: To obtain this Throphy you are going to need to find a Lich Tower and kill the Twilight Lich.

betterquesting.name: Minoshroom [E]
betterquesting.desc: To obtain this Throphy you are going to need to find a Labyrinth and kill the Minoshroom.

betterquesting.name: Knight Phantom [E]
betterquesting.desc: To obtain this Throphy you are going to need to find a Goblin Knight Stronghold and kill the Knight Phantom.

betterquesting.name: Hydra [E]
betterquesting.desc: To obtain this Throphy you are going to need to find a Hydra Lair and kill the Hydra.

betterquesting.name: Ur-Ghast [E]
betterquesting.desc: To obtain this Throphy you are going to need to find a Dark Tower and kill the Ur-Ghast.

betterquesting.name: The Beneath [E]
betterquesting.desc: The Beneath is a mining dimension. Whatever you do, try to always stay in the light.

betterquesting.name: Alpha Yeti [E]
betterquesting.desc: Find a Yeti Lair and kill an Alpha Yeti it to obtain its Fur.

betterquesting.name: Snow Queen [E]
betterquesting.desc: To obtain this Throphy you are going to need to find an Ice Tower and kill the Snow Queen.

betterquesting.name: Giant Problems [E]
betterquesting.desc: Find a Giant Cloud and kill the miner to obtain his Pickaxe, with which you'll be able to mine Giant Obsidian in a Troll Cave and obtain the Lamp of Cinders.

betterquesting.name: Soul Cages [RU]
betterquesting.desc:
By building a 3x3 structure with Glowstone in the middle, Blocks of Quartz on the sides and Obsidian in the edges and right-clicking the Glowstone with a Diamond, you will gain a Soul Shard. The more times you kill a certain mob with it in your inventory, the more it will level up.

 Once it's at least Tier 1 you can put it in a Soul Cage in order to spawn the mob you killed that many times, but you won't have the perks you'd have if it's a higher Tier.

betterquesting.name: Seared Furnace [T]
betterquesting.desc: The Seared Furnace is a large multiblock Furnace powered by Lava.

betterquesting.name: Tinker Tank [T]
betterquesting.desc: The Tinker Tank is a large multiblock Tank that can store multiple fluids at a time without them mixing.

betterquesting.name: Thermal Evaporator [IM]
betterquesting.desc: The Thermal Evaporator is a multiblock which can contiuously turn Water into Brine, making it great for automation.

betterquesting.name: Sulfurous Acid [PtAL]
betterquesting.desc:
Sulfurous Acid is needed for the multiblock Battery from Zetta Industries.

 You can making a 3x3 area with a Block of Sulfur in the middle and Water on the sides and edges and lighting the Block of Sulfur on Fire.

betterquesting.name: Battery [PtAL]
betterquesting.desc: The multiblock Battery just stores a large amount of power.

betterquesting.name: Turbine Generator [PtAL]
betterquesting.desc:
The Turbine Generator is a multiblock that doesn't have a determined shape, but has a minimum and maximum amount of components.

 It uses certain fluids to generate power.

betterquesting.name: Creating Syngas [PtAL]
betterquesting.desc: Syngas is made by mixing Water and Coal in the Syngas Producer and is used for generating power in the Steam Generator.

betterquesting.name: Steam Turbine Generator [PtAL]
betterquesting.desc: The Steam Turbine Generator uses Steam or Syngas to generate power.

betterquesting.name: Tank [PtAL]
betterquesting.desc: The multiblock Tank can store a set amount of a certain fluid, depending on how many Tank Blocks it has.

betterquesting.name: Passivly Cooled Reactor [PtAL]
betterquesting.desc: You can add a Coolant Port to your Extreme Reactor to cool it with Water, but you could also add another one and right-click it with an Extreme Wrench to output Steam from your Reactor, use it in a Turbine and then pipe it back in as Water.

betterquesting.name: Heat Exchanger [PtAL]
betterquesting.desc: The Heat Exchanger uses Lava to heat up Water and generate Steam, but also slowly generates Obsidian.

betterquesting.name: Worktable [LitF]
betterquesting.desc: The Worktable allows you to switch between conflicting recipes and can remember up to 9 recipes at a time.

betterquesting.name: Calculator Upgrades [SM]
betterquesting.desc: You can make upgrades for your Calculator machines.

betterquesting.name: Atomic Multiplier [SM]
betterquesting.desc:
Killing Chaos Dragons that get harder and harder the farther you go for obtaining Chaos Shards isn't fun. Luckly, you can now craft an Atomic Multiplier. 

 The Atomic Multiplier allows you to quadruple stackable items at the cost of 1.5GRF and 7 Circuits. Keep in mind that creative items, Legendary rewards and items from Extended Crafting and Modular Machinery are blacklisted.

betterquesting.name: Holographic Guide [E]
betterquesting.desc: The Holo-Projector allows you to see what's required for constructing Advanced Rocketry machines.

betterquesting.name: Hatches [E]
betterquesting.desc: To construct Advanced Rocketry multiblocks, you are going to need Hatches for inputting and outputting items and fluids and Plugs for inputting and outputting power.

betterquesting.name: Electric Arc Furnace [E]
betterquesting.desc: The Electric Arc Furnace allows you to make Silicon from Sand as well as a few, less useful alloys.

betterquesting.name: Crystallizer [E]
betterquesting.desc: The Multiblock Crystallizer is used for making Silicon Boule.

betterquesting.name: Cutting Machine [E]
betterquesting.desc: The multiblock Cutting Machine is used for making Silicon Wafers from Silicon Boule and AR Circuits from Circuit Plates.

betterquesting.name: Precision Assembler [E]
betterquesting.desc: The Precision Assembler allows you to make Circuit Plates and items needed for space exploration and to easily make AR Circuits Boards.

betterquesting.name: Rolling Machine [E]
betterquesting.desc: The multiblock Rolling Machine is used for making Sheets and Pressure Tanks.

betterquesting.name: Separating Water [PtAL]
betterquesting.desc: The Electrolyzer allows you to separate Water into Oxygen and Hydrogen.

betterquesting.name: Rocket Fuel [E]
betterquesting.desc: Rocket Fuel can be made from Oxygen and Hydrogen in a multiblock Chemical Reactor.

betterquesting.name: Gas Charge Pad [E]
betterquesting.desc: The Gas Charge Pad allows you to charge the Pressure Tanks in your Space Suit with Hydrogen and Oxygen.

betterquesting.name: Building A Rocket [E]
betterquesting.desc:
To build a Rocket, you are first going to need a Launch Pad. You need a square or rectangle of Launch Pad blocks, which determine how long and wide your Rocket will be, a pillar of Structure Blocks connected to it, which determine how high your Rocket will be and a Rocket Assembling Machine a block above and in front of your Launch Pad, that allows you to assemble your Rocket.

 Your Rocket can contain practically any block in the game, but it must have a few Fuel Powered Engines, Fuel Tanks, a Guidance Computer and a Seat.

betterquesting.name: Space Suit [E]
betterquesting.desc: To Survive In Space, you are going to need a Space Suit with Pressure Tanks on it that you can add with the Modular Workbench. The Modular Workbench can also be used for adding different modules for better travelling or information gathering.

betterquesting.name: The Moon [E]
betterquesting.desc:
Once you've built and fueled up your Rocket, you are almost ready for going to the Moon. All that's left to do is adding a Planet ID Chip to it, selecting the Moon/Luna and blasting off.

 On the Moon you an find all the resources that there'd normally be in the Overworld, but most importantly, Dilithium.

betterquesting.name: Space Station [E]
betterquesting.desc:
To make a Space Station, you are going to need to build it on a Launch Pad where the Rocket Assembly Machine is replaced with a Stalite Builder. You need to put a Satelite ID Chip and a Satelite Bay in it to build your Space Station.

 Put the Space Station Container in the Satelite Bay of a Rocket to send it into orbit and put the ID Chip of the Space Station in the Guidance Computer of a Rocket to travel to it.

betterquesting.name: Ventilation [E]
betterquesting.desc: So that you don't have to wear a Space Suit in your Space Station, you can put CO2 Scubbers with Carbon Collection Cartridges next to Oxygen Vents and it'll fill up with oxygen.

betterquesting.name: Warping Through Space [E]
betterquesting.desc: The Warp Core allows you to warp to other planets at the cost of Dilithium. To select your destination, you need to have a Warp Controller somewhere near it.

betterquesting.name: Energetic Sheep [CM]
betterquesting.desc:
Regular Sheep can be turned into Energetic Sheep when struck by Lightning, but they also have a small chance of spawning in your passive mob farm.

 You can shear them to get Energetic Wool, with which you can right-click your machines to power them, you can breed them and have a chance of getting another one, or you can fill them up with power by using a World Energy Exporter.

betterquesting.name: Energetic Shears [CM]
betterquesting.desc:
Once you've obtained 8 Energetic Wool, you can craft Energetic Shears, which collect more energy from Energetic Sheep, but don't give you Energetic Wool.

 Just like with Energetic Wool, you can right-click machines with them to transfer power to them.

betterquesting.name: Master Alloying [O]
betterquesting.desc:
The multiblock Master Alloy Furnace uses a lot of power to make alloys, that you'd usually make in the Smeltery, in a single tick.

 You will however need to upgrade its parts to make all alloys and to make them more efficiently.

betterquesting.name: Basic Machine Parts [O]
betterquesting.desc: These are the basic parts needed for constructing Modular Machines.

betterquesting.name: Changing The Land [VM]
betterquesting.desc: With your Mana Pool you can make special Seeds that, when used on Dirt, will turn it into another block.

betterquesting.name: Horns [VM]
betterquesting.desc: You can craft Horns that, when used, will destroy certain blocks nearby.

betterquesting.name: Hitting The Drums [VM]
betterquesting.desc: Instead of manually using Horns, you can make Horns that will be activated when hit with a Mana Burst.

betterquesting.name: Passive Mana Generation [VM]
betterquesting.desc: The Ring of Aura passivly generates Mana when worn.

betterquesting.name: Alchemy Catalyst [VM]
betterquesting.desc: The Alchemy Catalyst, when placed below your Mana Pool, allows you to transmute many more items with it.

betterquesting.name: Conjuration Catalyst [VM]
betterquesting.desc: The Conjuration Catalyst, when placed below your Mana Pool, allows you to duplicate certain items with it.

betterquesting.name: Mana Blaster [VM]
betterquesting.desc: Mana Blasters are in theory portable Mana Spreaders i.e. you can use them to manually shoot Mana Bursts.

betterquesting.name: Incense Sticks [VM]
betterquesting.desc: You can infuse Incense Sticks with a potion effect with the Botanical Brewery and put it on an Incense Plate to apply that potion effect to all players in a 30 block radius.

betterquesting.name: Tainted Blood Pendant [VM]
betterquesting.desc: Tainted Blood Pendants can be infused with a potion effect with the Botanical Brewery and when worn, as long as you have enough Mana, you will have that potion effect applied to you.

betterquesting.name: Luminizers [VM]
betterquesting.desc: Luminizers can be used as an interesting way of traveling around your base.

betterquesting.name: Ender Energy Manipulator [O]
betterquesting.desc: To obtain Dragon Eggs from Ender Dragons, you are going to need Ender Energy Manipulators.

betterquesting.name: Energy Infuser [O]
betterquesting.desc: The Energy Infuser Charges items faster than anything else.

betterquesting.name: Advanced Dislocator [O]
betterquesting.desc: The Advanced Dislocator allows you to instantly teleport to a certain, already specified place.

betterquesting.name: Evironmental Modifiers [ET]
betterquesting.desc: With Mica you can make Speed, Piezo and Accuracy Modifiers with which you can replace the Null Modifiers of your ET multiblocks to upgrade them.

betterquesting.name: Heavy Water
betterquesting.desc: Heavy Water can be obtained by pumping out Water with an Electric Pump with a Filter Upgrade.

betterquesting.name: Automating The Tables [O]
betterquesting.desc: The Automation Interface allows you to automate all the different Extended Crafting Tables, provided that it has power.

betterquesting.name: You've Got Mail! [LitF]
betterquesting.desc: If you're playing on a server, you could send items to people in a Letter, even when they aren't online. If you aren't, I guess you could send yourself a Letter.

betterquesting.name: Compact Systems [DS]
betterquesting.desc: The ME Capability Adaptor allows you to connect your ME system with whatever is inside a Compact Machine, by having one inside of it, next to a Tunnel and one next to it, on the corresponding side of the block.

betterquesting.name: Advanced Ember Transferring [AMM]
betterquesting.desc: The Ember Spread Burst allows you to separately output Ember from all of its sides and the Ember Funnel quickly collects Ember from multiple Ember Ejectors.

betterquesting.name: End Stone [MR]
betterquesting.desc: You can make End Stone through combustion, with a Floating Crystal linked to Sandstone or in a Fluid Transposer with Resonant Ender.

betterquesting.name: Dark Matter Warper [MR]
betterquesting.desc: The Dark Matter Warper uses Dark Matter to trasmute mobs around it into other mobs. It also damages players when they are near it.

betterquesting.name: Completely Automating Combustion
betterquesting.desc: The Smart Combustion Controller allows you to fully automate combustion by selecting which items can be made in it. The items closer to the left will be made first and it can do 10 recipes/s.

betterquesting.name: White Matter [MR]
betterquesting.desc: Light Matter machines are the most efficient, but use Light Matter to work.

betterquesting.name: The Cold Never Bothered Me Anyway [MR]
betterquesting.desc: The Light Matter Freezer is the best Freezer in the game.

betterquesting.name: A Safer Portal [MR]
betterquesting.desc: You can add a few blocks to your End Portal Core to get rid of those pests.

betterquesting.name: Attracting Animals [MR]
betterquesting.desc: The Wildlife Attractor uses power, Water, and Plant Matter to attract animals on top of it.

betterquesting.name: Health Gem [MR]
betterquesting.desc: You can shift+right-click with the Health Gem to fill it up with Life Points and while in your inventory, for every 50 life points it has, you'll get an extra heart.

betterquesting.name: Life Injector [MR]
betterquesting.desc: You can put a Health Gem in a Life Injector in order to fill it up with the health from the mobs on top of it.

betterquesting.name: Automatic Life Infusion [MR]
betterquesting.desc: You can build a multiblock Life Infuser in order to automate the life infusion process.

betterquesting.name: Villagers [MR]
betterquesting.desc: Find 2 Zombie Villagers, throw a Potion of Weakness at them and feed them a Golden Apple to turn them into Villagers. Put them in an area that has a lot of Doors with blocks above them and you've got a vanilla Villager farm. There are far better modded alternatives to that though.

betterquesting.name: Illagers [MR]
betterquesting.desc: The Dark Matter Warper will turn Zombie Villagers into Illagers (Vindicators and Evokers).

betterquesting.name: Ember Modifiers [AMM]
betterquesting.desc:
You can add an Ancient Motive Core to tools that are on a Dawnstone Anvil for them to start gaining heat when used.

 After they've gained a good amount of heat, you can drop them into an Inferno Forge to add a modifier slot to them and then you'll be able to add certain modifiers to them with the Dawnstone Anvil.

betterquesting.name: End Stone Machines [MR]
betterquesting.desc: End Stone Machines have evened out stats and use Ender Pearls instead of fuel.

betterquesting.name: The Nether [MR]
betterquesting.desc:
Now that you have Steel, you can make a Flint and Steel to go to make a Nether portal.

 Note: You need to craft a Flint and Steel to get access to the Nether, so every member in a team needs to craft one to enter it.

 While it may be a void, you can use the Nether for making Gold farms, but most importantly, for obtaining Blaze Rods from Blazes which only spawn on Netherrack.

betterquesting.name: Sugarcanes [MR]
betterquesting.desc:
Sugarcanes can be made from Glistering Melons through life infusion. To make Glistering Melons however, you are going to need either a Chemical Reactor or a Starlight Infuser.

 They provide you with the most efficient way of making Sugar and allow you to make a few other items.

betterquesting.name: Fishing For Saplings [MR]
betterquesting.desc: The Survivalist's Fishing Rod is a fast unbreakable Fishing Rod that can fish out junk, Wood, Dirt and Saplings.

betterquesting.name: You Are Really Crushing It!
betterquesting.desc: The Compressed Rock Crusher is faster and more efficient than the regular one and can grind compressed blocks.

betterquesting.name: Compressed Cactus
betterquesting.desc: The Compressed Cactus gives you more Cactus Needles for less hearts, does a large amount of damage to mobs, can have Water extracted from it, can be cut (you can use a Compressed Knife on it) for getting 18 Cactus Fruit and can be grown on Compressed Sand.

betterquesting.name: Knives [MR]
betterquesting.desc: Knives can be used for catting Cacti into Cactus Fruit and Melons (the blocks) into Melons (the items).

betterquesting.name: Fixtures [DS]
betterquesting.desc: Instead of havng them as full blocks, you can turn ME Drives and Storage Cells into Fixtures that have a bit more than half the storage space, but can can share a block space with Cables, Terminals,...

betterquesting.name: Extra Lives 3
betterquesting.desc: Through this quest you can exchange 3 Rare Loot Chests for a Quarter Heart.

betterquesting.name: Sluice Box [Easy-Only] [IT]
betterquesting.desc: You can use the Iron Hammer on Ores on the Crushing Table to obtain Rocky Chunks, which can be used on a Sluice Box with Water for doubling the amount of ingots you get and for a chance of getting a different extra metal.

betterquesting.name: Extra Lives 2
betterquesting.desc: Through this quest you can exchange 5 Uncommon  Loot Chests for a Quarter Heart.

betterquesting.name: Extra Lives 4
betterquesting.desc: Through this quest you can exchange 3 Epic Loot Chests for a Half Heart.

betterquesting.name: Extra Lives 5
betterquesting.desc: Through this quest you can exchange a Legendary Loot Chest for an Extra Life.

betterquesting.name: Extra Lives 1
betterquesting.desc: If you're playing in Hardcore Questing Mode (enabled by doing /bq_user hardcore), through this quest you can exchange 5 Basic Loot Chests for a Quarter Heart.

betterquesting.desc: You can replace some basic cooking ingredients with their Hemp versions.
